data.text: @Wray62 @godofradio @AZDHS I read that have major problems finding like 20 mill units....that somehow got lost... i truly hope that gets resolved
@godofradio @AZDHS I can’t emphasize enough how happy I am to hear that! Good news is...good!

Can't say enough great things about @AZDHS who is moving right along with shots, the scientists and researchers and manufacturers who made this possible, and the taxpayers who made this happen. Thank you ALL from the bottom of my heart.
#COVIDVaccination

After being fine all day today, with no symptoms other than some mild fatigue, I think that about covers it! Overall experience with Shot 2 was just as the literature suggested: Pain for a day, aches for a day, and fatigue for two days. And that's it! #COVIDVaccination

For now, at V2+40 hours, I feel like a new man. Bit weak from yesterday's achiness and malaise but otherwise all is well. All vitals are back to normal and those obnoxious flu-like symptoms are long gone!
#COVIDVaccination

Female peer mentioned swollen glands, none of the rest of us had them. But it did sort of feel like one in the left armpit, near the injection site. To me that seemed more muscular. Either way, that pain completely disappeared by V2+40 hours. 
#COVIDVaccination

One of my peers described it as feeling "like being hit by a truck." Another said "it feels like being hung over." She's a lot more exciting than I am. 😂
#COVIDVaccination
Lots of exhaustion from V2+9 hours all the way through V2+33 hours. Almost exactly 24 hours of achiness and fatigue and then, as suddenly as it had started, it was gone.

V2+14 hours brought the headache, which felt at first like sinuses but then went around the crown of the skull. This began to fade around V2+20 hours. Still no fever or chills or nausea to speak of. Left arm MUCH less sore than round 1!
#COVIDVaccination

At V2+9 hours, the aches began. Mild, persistent aching throughout the body. Made it uncomfortable so sleep was diminished, but was never untenable. Pulse went from 60s to 90s but no fever to note. Felt like getting the flu, minus the flu part. 😂
#COVIDVaccination

V2+6 hours and my left arm feels slightly stiff, but nowhere near as painful as last time. No other symptoms at all.
#CovidVaccine 
#COVIDVaccination

This made sense when I got to the head of the line. I was polled on any reactions, side effects, or evil spirits that bedeviled me after the 1st shot. They noted it all down, and the needle went into the exact same spot. No pain! 
#CovidVaccine 
#COVIDVaccination

So the line today was longer, which is good! Many people happily waiting their turn. We were divided i to 1st shot and 2nd shot lines, the former moved much faster than the latter.
#CovidVaccine 
#COVIDVaccination

Time to reconvene for round 2! Time for the second and final #CovidVaccine shot. Let's hope this goes well!
#COVIDVaccination

V+71 hours, nothing to report! It is as though nothing ever happened. None of my peers reported the same tachycardia I experienced, so that seems to be a "me" issue. Will monitor another 25 hours, but this might be it for this round. 😁😁 Awesome! #COVIDVaccination

At V+53 hours all is well, so hopefully that holds through the night. No fever, no arm pain even at the injection site, no symptoms other than fatigue from last night's poor sleep. Come on, antibodies! 😁
#COVIDVaccination

Either way, I'm alive and feeling good now! This has been the only really unpleasant issue with the #COVIDVaccination and from what I'm hearing, not many of us have had this. I wouldn't let this dissuade you or anyone you know. 😁

One tantalizing clue: The pulse and left arm pain were directly and inversely proportionate. As the arm pain faded, the pulse went up. I now have zero arm pain, but pulse (while off its high) is still slightly elevated at 82 versus the normal 67.
#COVIDVaccination

Throughout last night tachycardia was an issue. It seemed too late to be anything anyphlactic so my guess (backed up by the awesome Dr. @Medullosa!) is that this was the immune response going into high gear: I have a history of this right before I get sick. 
#COVIDVaccination

Here is where things get weird. At V+33 hours I sat down to relax. Pulse felt high. I checked and it was 99. Checked my tracker and it had been in the 90's for a few hours prior though I'd been busy and hadn't noticed. 
#COVIDVaccination
@godofradio Oh I’m sorry. Did I punch too hard?
@MissRosieDovah You are the kindest sister. 😂😂😂
@godofradio https://t.co/Q57cepRm70
@MissRosieDovah You certainly can, though hopefully not too hard. 😂
@godofradio So what ur saying is that I can punch U now

Around V+30 hours I seems to have more motion in the left arm. The soreness decreased and there was less pain on contact at the injection site.
#COVIDVaccination

V+26 hours brought a very faint, very mild achiness in lower back and knees. I imagine this is what Doc was talking about, but I'm not sure I'd even have noticed if I wasn't looking specifically for it. Temperature and all vitals remain perfectly normal!
#COVIDVaccination
@AZweatherchick Well, you know you've got a lot going on so I certainly wouldn't hold it against ya! 😁
@AZweatherchick No, no, I was merely pining away for one back when mine was falling apart 😂
@AZweatherchick Doing great! I've actually always had one, go figure. 😂

At V+20 hours:  Doc had told me to expect "chills, aches, possibly nausea" at this point. I have none of that. Arm feels bruised if I touch it, feels muscularly sore if I move it...and that's it! One of my peers seems to have it worse & is using ibuprofen, I havent needed it yet.

Arm pain is unusual because ice packs seem to do nothing, while warm packs/cloths definitely help. Seems counterintuitive but try heat first.
#COVIDVaccination

Slept between V+8 hours and V+14 hours and had no major issues. Noticed pain 2x in left shoulder and upper arm while sleeping on that side, rolling over resolved it. Arm pain was moderate, it was heavy, stiff, and moderately painful to move immediately after waking.

To answer two questions posed:  
1. Yes, temperature has been consistently normal throughout. No fever.
2. No, I've not had any tachycardia at any point. Pulse has remained normal with the exception of when I was signing the pre-shot waiver.
#COVIDVaccination

V+7 hours, left arm feels heavy and sore, but is manageable. Warm washcloth helps. I can move it in all directions, it is just sore when I do so. Feels more like a bruise now. No other symptoms at all! 
#COVIDVaccination

Sometime after V+4 hours, left arm felt sore when I moved it to lift something. Not a bruised feeling or like I was punched, but like I spent too much time in the gym on Arm Day. (And when has that ever been the case?!) 😂
#COVIDVaccination
@Arithered Are your sign-ups being managed by the state or the county? It might be time for you to pre-register already!

@godofradio That's good! I think I'm a Phase 1B critical worker (in-person teacher), so it's possible I might be able to get vaccinated somewhere at the halfway point of the rollout, whenever that ends up being.
@Arithered Group 1A is still being worked through, but they told me today that 1B/essential employees are about to be scheduled. Definitely a good sign!
@godofradio Yes, thank you! It's encouraging to know that they have a system in place. Here in PA we're still only vaccinating healthcare workers.

@Arithered Hope I answered this for you, my friend. They put my information into an electronic records system to track my appointments. Also encouraged me to use an app the CDC is using to monitor side effects, etc.

At V+2 hours, I felt a very vague heaviness in the left shoulder, only while moving it. No pain, dizziness, tingling, fatigue, or any other symptoms at all.
#COVIDVaccination

I'd heard reports of post-shot tachycardia and numbness/swelling. None of this happened to me. Pulse was 72 on arrival, 89 when I filled out the "this might kill you but probably won't form, and back to 74 at the time of injection. O2 sats were never below 98, fully masked.

At this point they scheduled me for the 2nd shot, which will be in exactly 21 days. They warned me not to cancel or modify that because the timing needs to be precise. I told them I wouldn't do so for all the salsa in Phoenix. 
#COVIDVaccination @Arithered

Arriving at the monitoring site i was met by a nurse and two student nurses from a community college 60 miles away. They chatted me up while explaining what to expect over next few days (aches, pains, perhaps nausea). They were WONDERFUL young ladies. The future is bright, folks.

About this time, some 40 seconds post-shot, I felt a faint, mild tingling in my left forearm and fingers. It went away as I drove to the post-shot monitoring area. I was vaguely aware that my left shoulder felt "heavy" as I turned the steering wheel. But there was no pain at all.

As soon as this was done, the doc placed a post-it note on my car with  a time on it. That time was 15 minutes from the injection. He explained I'd need to be monitored that long and directed me to a queue of cars to wait out that duration.
#COVIDVaccination

"Let's see that deltoid!" The needle was an inch long but small-gauge. I looked away for a second and when I turned back the doc was withdrawing the needle. I hadn't felt a thing! (I DID feel the seasonal flu shot months ago.) It was very quick.
#COVIDVaccination
@godofradio Congratulations! How do they go about making sure you can get the second vaccine, or that you know when and where to get it?

Cars are directed into a covered area overflowing with doctors. Without delving into operational details, I could see how the vaccine was stored and brought over to individual injection points. A doc approached and said what to expect and what to watch out for.
#COVIDVaccination

I am very impressed by how smooth everything went. It is a well-oiled machine. Cars lined up into multiple queues with med staff beside them. First comes check-in, then med questionnaire, then release of liability, and then "the room."

#COVIDVaccination
@godofradio Super eager to hear nothing 🤞🤞

My left arm is full of hope. 

#COVIDVaccination
For now, I am headed to the vaccination site, which is a drive-up location in a massive parking lot. Updates will follow. #COVIDVaccination
@rustysunshine Thank you SO much! I'll let you know how it goes in the days ahead! 😍 Stay safe, sweet one.

I understand this topic may not be for everyone so I will not be at all hurt if you mute this thread. This is mainly intended as a way to help people know what to expect. If you have others who are curious, please feel free to pass this info along. #vaccine #COVIDVaccination
@godofradio I'm happy for you ❤️ May it go easy on you!
